OL,6,FSir Brandon, who was secretary of
OL,7,Fstate at the time, said ministers had
OL,8,Fbecome frustrated with each other.
OL,10,FHe told the inquiry: "I do remember
OL,11,Fduring that period being concerned
OL,12,Fthat I could see the Executive
OL,13,Fcollapsing again.
OL,15,F"One of the ministers had been talking
OL,16,Fabout resigning, just out of
OL,17,Ffrustration at how things were
OL,18,Fhappening.
