OL,6,FThe conversation had focused on the
OL,7,Fneed for consistent messaging between
OL,8,Fthe two jurisdictions in the fight
OL,9,Fagainst Covid.
OL,11,FBut the following day, the Irish
OL,12,FGovernment announced it was going to
OL,13,Fclose schools.
OL,15,FLead counsel for the inquiry Clair
OL,16,FDobbin KC asked if this had become a
OL,17,F"cause of some difficulty" for
OL,18,Fministers in the Stormont powersharing
OL,19,FExecutive.
